Coca-Cola to Invest 4.9 Billion Shillings in Kenya, Nation Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-04-12T04:08:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/coca-cola-to-invest-4-9-billion-shillings-in-kenya-nation-says.html
Coca-Cola Co. (KO)  plans to invest 4.9
billion shillings ($58.2 million) in  Kenya  over the next three
years amid increased competition in the East African soft-drinks
market, the  Daily Nation  reported.  The company will upgrade equipment, expand capacity and
increase juice production, the Nairobi-based newspaper said,
citing Eurasia-Africa Group President Ahmet Bozer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  